---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About — LuckyToss"
	description="LuckyToss is a free, browser-based dice roller and coin flip simulator. Learn how it works and why it's free."
	canonicalPath="/about"
>
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
		<h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[#2B2013]">
			About LuckyToss
		</h1>
		<div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-[#5C4F3D]">
			<p>
				LuckyToss is a single-purpose tool for rolling animated dice or
				flipping an animated 3D coin — entirely inside your web browser.
				Every result comes from
				<strong class="text-[#2B2013]">Math.random()</strong>, so outcomes are
				fair and unbiased, and nothing is ever sent to a server.
			</p>
			<p>
				Because there is no server-side processing, LuckyToss can stay
				completely free with no account, no signup, and no limits. The site
				is supported by on-page advertising.
			</p>
			<p>
				LuckyToss tracks your streaks, tallies, and a short recent history
				for both the coin flip and the dice roller, so you can see patterns
				across a session without anything being saved once you close the tab.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
